saṃyutta nikāya 45
14. oghavagga
171. oghasutta
sāvatthinidānaṃ.
“cattārome, bhikkhave, oghā.
katame cattāro?
kāmogho, bhavogho, diṭṭhogho, avijjogho—
ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro oghā.
imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ oghānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya … pe … ayaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvetabbo”ti.
(yathā esanā, evaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)
paṭhamaṃ.
